		{"id":"legend","type":"text","text":"LEGEND (this needs work)\n\ncyan   = vault file (exists, clickable)\norange = external / to import\npurple = annotation (image, quote card, comment)\nno color = transition\nred (provisional...im interested in segregating me and the ai and having me always comment and contextualize its input= ai/agent  ","x":0,"y":-1000,"width":340,"height":320},
		{"id":"51019e7b150733b9","type":"file","file":"_trace/story prefab.canvas","x":-431,"y":2037,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"t1","type":"text","text":"## hold skill\n\n---\n\n**AGENT**\nPhone ramble transcribed to journal. Hold skill runs: fragments selected and extended, five-page cinematic comic script drafted with per-panel image prompts. Nietzsche candidates researched. Cross-cut observation (\"visiting and not arriving\") written.\n\n---\n\n**YOU**\nHere im only interested in the comic script.  the other stuff is kept or interesting insofar as it maybe contributed to this particular script.  i tried many hold runs and saw many variations.  this one was 'lucky' somehow, or insightful or touched me in a way the others didnt.  It was also the first one (So maybe i imprinted), but i mean to suggest that this is a big leap already....lots of iterations or sampling could happen here.\n\nI would say that as a pattern sonnet did seem to focus on not giving up the suede jacket as an important thematic point. it also trimmed the fat from the larger notes consistently well.  and kept to the important bits from the prompt ask in the journal.  so maybe a pattern pulled from multiple scripts to get the through lines would reduce the luck part.  the story structure i pulled gave me a skeleton to groove with and hate and reshape based on my own signals.  intangible threads may not have got my motor started in the same way ","x":-400,"y":840,"width":640,"height":520},
		{"id":"hold","type":"file","file":"_reflection/2026-04-22-holdv04test.md","x":320,"y":-160,"width":680,"height":1150,"color":"5"},
		{"id":"d46e77fbfe466eb4","type":"text","text":"IDEA\ncould we write a narrative about comic this process?  would it be a substack or a blog post?","x":478,"y":-2320,"width":250,"height":198},
